-- CTC Media 4 Years and Over Russian Audience Share Falls to 7.4%
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-03-29T17:32:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/ctc-media-4-years-and-over-russian-audience-share-falls-to-7-4-.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily
share of viewers four-years-old and over fell to 7.4 percent in
the week to March 25, after gaining the previous week, data
compiled by TNS-Global shows.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, fell from 7.5 percent in
the week to March 18, data researcher TNS-Global said in an e-
mail today. Among audiences 18 years and above, CTC remained the
fifth-most popular channel with 6.2 percent viewer share, down
from 6.5 percent the previous week, the data show.  NTV Television maintained the biggest average daily
audience share in Russia. NTV’s audience fell to 15.1 percent in
the week to March 25, from 15.4 percent a week earlier, while
 Russia ’s Pervyi Kanal, which is controlled by the government,
had a 14.2 percent share, compared with 14.9 percent in the
previous period. Rossiya-1 had a 12.2 percent of average daily
share of viewers four-years-old and over in the week to March
25, compared with 12.1 percent in the previous week, TNS-Global
said.  NTV, Pervyi, the Rossiya-1 channel and TNT were all ahead
of CTC among viewers ages 18 and over, TNS-Global said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
